HEADWORD: Cœnenchyma
<hw>C⟦oe⟧*nen"chy*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL. <ets>coenenchyma</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>koino`s</grk> common +
<?/ something poured in. Formed like <ets>parenchyma</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The common tissue which unites the polyps or
zooids of a compound anthozoan or coral. It may be soft or more or less
ossified. See <er>Coral</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coenesthesis</ent>⟦br⟧
